        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 5:41PM PDT by NWS Pendleton OR</headline>
        <description>At 541 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southeast of Starkey, or 15 miles northwest of North Powder,
moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
La Grande and Island City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
